Linking words and phrases

When we want to add an idea, we can use words and phrases that link the ideas together. 
Words and phrases such as moreover, furthermore, in addition, as well as that, what is more, also 
are linking words and phrases. 
Use a comma after the linking words and phrases. 

Furthermore, there are several other issues to discuss.

In addition, we will be discussing several other issues.

Moreover, we need to discuss other issues.

Also, we haven't discussed some of the other issues.

